UNIVERSITY OF MORATUWA, SRI LANKA
Faculty of Engineering
Department of Electronic and Telecommunication Engineering

Semester 7 (Intake 2020)
EN4314 - Telecommunication Core Networks
Continuous Assessment 2 – Case Study

Pushpakumara S. N. – 200489H
Pramuditha A. A. H. – 200476P
Satharasinghe S. A. P. U. – 200589N

Dharmasri N. T. S – 200126U
This report is submitted as a partial fulfillment for module EN4314 - Telecommunication Core Networks,
Department of Electronic and Telecommunication Engineering, University of Moratuwa.

1
1. Prepare a list of questions that you would ask from Super Tel in order to do the design.
Here, the questionnaire is formed based on the position/ job role of the of the person to

whom this will be presented.
To CTO (Chief Technical Officer):
• What is your expected timespan to make this project fully operational within the

desired country?
- Are there any specific time periods that we need to consider when
implementing a particular portion of the project? (As an example, what’re

the desirable time periods when implementing such a project within a
university or some specific enterprise?)
• After how many years of deployment, are you going to expand your service stack

(voice, broadband internet, IPTV, VoD)? (To decide the network devices and their end
of service/support information that we need for the deployment.)
• Since you have an existing underutilized fiber infrastructure in Europe, are you

planning to integrate it with new Asian operations? If so, have you done any
feasibility check on that and do you have a set of pre-defined technical
requirements for such integration?

- In this scenario, we need to identify the end points such as the European
gateway routers that we can use to access the internet from Asia or are
we going to establish gateway routers within Asia to access internet.

- What’re the possible locations that we can use to locate CLSs (Cabel
Landing Stations) to connect with the European fiber infrastructure.
• Do we have pre-existing vendor relationships that will extend to this region, or

should we seek new partnerships for hardware and software?
• Are there any specific security concerns that you have in terms of the network
design?

• Can you provide a resource person/ team who has a thorough understanding about
your legacy infrastructure to coordinate with us and resolve any further issues/
clarifications during the project?

• In how many phases are you going to carry out the implementations? (If we have a
clear understanding about the phases of this project, we can manage the design
works according to that)

• What are the other companies/entities that will be collaboratively working with us
during this project and what kind of services will they provide? (Will they be
responsible for core network security/ on-call support/ device installation etc.)

2
To CEO (Chief Executive Officer):
• Can you provide me with a rough budget that you’re going to allocate for this

project? (To get a rough idea about how broad & complex this project can be)
• Are there specific competitors in Asia whose strategies or services we aim to
counter or emulate? If so, are you aware of those strategies and special operations/

operators?
• What customer base size or revenue target would you define as a success for this
expansion?

• How does your company plan to differentiate itself from the other telecom
operators in Asia, especially in terms of pricing, services or customer experience?
To CMO (Chief Marketing Officer):

• Who are the primary target customers (residential or business, urban or rural)?
• Do you have any marketing strategies to promote your organization among the Asian
customers? (Do you wish to offer any occasional/ seasonal offers to customers like

unlimited internet access, free voice + SMS services, seasonal broadband
packages?)
• What customer acquisition and retention strategies have been identified for this

new market?
To CFO (Chief Financial Officer):
• Have you finalized with the total budget that you’re going to allocate for this Asian

expansion? How is it divided between infrastructure development (CapEx – Capital
Expenditure) and operations (OpEx – Operation Expenditure)? (We need an idea
about the budget allocation when choosing necessary devices and preparing BOM

– Bills of Material)
• What is the expected revenue projection for the starting year of this project? (To
achieve a high revenue for the company, the network should perform well.)

2. What are the factors to be considered for their Asian Expansion?
We can identify several categories regarding the factors that need to be considered for this
project.

3
• Social/ Cultural Factors – cultural diversity, customer preferences regarding
telecom support, local language support, social norms and behaviors, workforce

culture.
• Technological Factors – infrastructure compatibility, 5G and other emerging
technologies, local tech ecosystems, cybersecurity and data privacy, tech literacy

and technology adoption.
• Geographical Factors – network reach and connectivity, availability and reliability of
submarine cable infrastructure, natural disaster risks, urban vs rural deployment

challenges.
• Sustainability Factors – energy efficiency, carbon footprint, waste management,
corporate social responsibility.

• Power Factors – power availability and stability, energy costs, availability of
renewable energy sources, power consumption of services.
• Market Factors – competition, regulatory environment, pricing strategies, market

demand, local partnerships and collaborations.
Also, the existing services and the ones that are going to be established under this project
should be identified properly.

• Existing services offered by Super Tel – traditional voice services, broadband
internet, IPTV service, VoD services.
• New services that can be established under the Asian operation – mobile

broadband and 5G services, cloud and data center services, managed services and
cybersecurity, VoIP, CDN services, smart home services etc.
